os</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Stampe was born in 1486, in Bradfield, Berkshire, England, his father, John Stampe V, was 25 and his mother, Elizabeth Cox, was 26. He had at least 2 sons with Joan Knapp. He died about 1539, in his hometown, at the age of 54, and was buried in Bradfield, Berkshire, England."},"et":{"1486–about 1539":"1486–umbes 1539","1486–1539":"1486–1539","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1508–1558":"1508–1558","1515–1555":"1515–1555","1533–1595":"1533–1595","1534–1555":"1534–1555","1461–Male":"1461–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1481":"1481","1558":"1558","1534":"1534","about 1539":"umbes 1539","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1486":"1486","about 1534":"umbes 1534","1497":"1497","1595":"1595","about 1533":"umbes 1533","1508":"1508","1539":"1539","1515":"1515","Bradfield, Berkshire, England":"Bradfield, Berkshire, England","Peasemore, Berkshire, England":"Peasemore, Berkshire, England","Burford, Oxfordshire, England":"Burford, Oxfordshire, England","St. Giles' Church, Colchester, Essex, England":"Colchester St Giles, Colchester, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1486–about 1539":"1486–noin 1539","1486–1539":"1486–1539","1497–1558":"1497–1558","1508–1558":"1508–1558","1515–1555":"1515–1555","1533–1595":"1533–1595","1534–1555":"1534–1555","1461–Male":"1461–Kuollut","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1481":"1481","1558":"1558","1534":"1534","about 1539":"noin 1539","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1486":"1486","about 1534":"noin 1534","1497":"1497","1595":"1595","about 1533":"noin 1533","1508":"1508","1539":"1539","1515":"1515","Bradfield, Berkshire, England":"Bradfield, Berkshire, England","Peasemore, Berkshire, England":"Peasemore, Berkshire, Engla